From any vertex except $E$, the frog jumps to one of the two adjacent vertices. When it reaches $E$, it stops. We need to prove that $a_{2n-1} = 0$, meaning there are no paths of exactly $2n-1$ jumps ending at $E$.

Looking at the code structure, we have:
